            <description><![CDATA[<h2>ChainLink 0.3.665</h2>
<p class="sub">Everything from 0.3.663, plus two additions to the ride graph and your records.</p>

<h3>New since 0.3.663</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Zoom the performance graph and the averages follow.</strong> Drag to
  select a climb, a sprint or an interval and the legend reports the averages for
  <em>that section</em> — power, heart rate, speed, elevation — rather than the
  whole ride. The selection is tinted and labelled with its length so it can't be
  mistaken for the ride average. Reset to go back to the full ride.</li>
  <li><strong>Career Bests are clickable.</strong> Each record now names the ride
  that set it and opens straight to it, so you can check a number rather than
  take it on trust.</li>
</ul>

<h3>And everything from 0.3.663</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Your fitness signature now goes down as well as up.</strong> It follows
  your training load rather than remembering a good day forever — keep training and
  it holds, ease off and it drifts, and a hard effort pushes it back up. Each energy
  system moves at its own pace.</li>
  <li><strong>Breakthrough badges</strong> on rides that genuinely raised your fitness,
  a <strong>Breakthroughs</strong> page under Fitness showing what each one moved, and
  a <strong>Career Bests</strong> record that never decays.</li>
  <li><strong>The same numbers on every device</strong>, worked out from your rides
  rather than copied between them — and <strong>no Mac required</strong>.</li>
  <li>Dodgy power spikes from a dying battery or sensor glitch no longer pollute your
  power curve or peak power.</li>
  <li>If anything ever looks wrong: <strong>Settings → Maintenance → Recompute fitness
  data</strong>. Safe, nothing is deleted, running it twice changes nothing.</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
