        <item>
            <title>0.3.663</title>
            <pubDate>Sun, 19 Jul 2026 14:52:51 -0700</pubDate>
            <sparkle:version>663</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>0.3.663</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>14.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <description><![CDATA[<h2>ChainLink 0.3.663</h2>
<p class="sub">Your fitness numbers now describe today — and they agree on every device.</p>

<p>This is a big one. If you have ever looked at your threshold and thought
"that isn't me any more", this release is the fix.</p>

<h3>Your fitness signature now changes with your training</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>It goes down as well as up.</strong> Previously your threshold, matchbook
  and peak power could only ever rise — a single great ride years ago set a number
  that never came back down. Now they follow your training load: keep training and
  they hold, ease off and they drift, and a hard effort pushes them back up.</li>
  <li><strong>Each energy system moves at its own pace</strong>, so a block of long
  steady miles keeps your endurance while your sharp edge fades — which is what
  actually happens.</li>
  <li><strong>All three numbers are now measured from your own riding</strong> rather
  than estimated from a starting guess.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Breakthroughs</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Rides that genuinely raised your fitness now get a <strong>gold, silver or
  bronze badge</strong> in your ride list, and there is a new
  <strong>Breakthroughs</strong> page under Fitness showing what each one moved.</li>
  <li>A new <strong>Career Bests</strong> card records your best ever effort at each
  duration. These never decay — they are a record of what you have done, kept
  separate from what you can do today.</li>
</ul>

<h3>The same numbers everywhere</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Your Mac, iPhone and iPad now show <strong>identical</strong> fitness numbers.
  They are worked out from your rides on each device rather than copied between
  them, so they cannot drift apart.</li>
  <li><strong>You no longer need a Mac.</strong> Ride detail and fitness analysis work
  the same on an iPhone or iPad alone.</li>
  <li>If your numbers ever look wrong: <strong>Settings → Maintenance → Recompute
  fitness data</strong>. It is safe, nothing is deleted, and running it twice
  changes nothing.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Fixes</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Dodgy power readings — the spikes you get from a dying battery or a sensor
  glitch — no longer pollute your power curve or peak power.</li>
  <li>The coach no longer describes an old peak as your current fitness.</li>
  <li>Faster, more accurate ride detail on phones and iPads.</li>
  <li>Various layout fixes on iPhone.</li>
</ul>

<p class="sub">Coming from 0.3.628? This includes everything since — quite a lot.</p>
]]></description>
